element.name: Ellenfield Park by AbbeyAckbar, Traditional Cache (3/1.5)

description.p: The park is located in Whitehall. It extends to 10 hectares and was developed in the late 1950's and early '60s to satisfy local demand for a sports area.

element.long-description:
The tennis courts & football training areas were recently upgraded & a childrens playground was recently constructed. Stealth is a must to retrieve the cache!

ul.li:
2010-05-17T19:00:00Z : Found it by evosheas
Our first Irish cache during our six week visit here from Australia to catch up with family. Brought along some young first timers and where i had given up, it was the youngers who found it. Very creative cache. First to sign the new logbook. Thanks heaps. Cheers.

2010-05-07T19:46:47Z : Enable Listing by AbbeyAckbar
Cache replaced at same co-ords and fixed so that it won't fall from it's location again. Updated the hint.

2010-05-03T11:29:37Z : Temporarily Disable Listing by AbbeyAckbar
Cache is in need of maintenance. Temporarily disabling it till we have it fixed.

2010-05-02T19:00:00Z : Found it by hollmanr
Found it after a few extra hints from Fitzet. Cache was not in its original hiding place and log was missing. Contacted Abbeyackbar and they plan to rectify this asap. We shall return to sign the log. TFTC

2010-04-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Toffee Man
Found this interesting cache this evening after searching for a while. There were loads of muggles watching a football match & a young child banging a ball against the wall beside us. We were just about to give up when BJ 59 spotted something unusual which turned out to be the "treasure". TFTC Toffee Man #296
